<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-174-328  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 174 328.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Feb 19 1990 v7 n8 p2(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>K mart upgrades national net to fight competitors. (multifacetednetwork will improve customer services)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brown, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>K mart Corp, with its $29 billion in retail sales, is hoping toimprove its corporate image by signing on celebrities to promotenew products and enhancing its customer services by upgrading itsnetwork.andP;  Complete installation of the very small apertureterminal (VSAT) network is anticipated by the end of 1990.andP;  K martis also upgrading from old IBM Series/1 minicomputers to UnisysCorp's 80486-based Series 6000 microcomputers for in-store trackand inventory purposes.andP;  The new network will support voice, dataand video.andP;  All of the K mart stores will be linked to the datacenter via the VSAT network.andP;  The network supportsvideoconferencing, credit authorization and batch processing,applications which will improve in-store customer service.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   K Mart Corp. (automation).andO;Ticker:    KM.andO;Topic:     RetailingUpgradingPromotion of ProductNetworksCustomer RelationsVery Small Aperture TerminalsMicrocomputers.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>